events.description: Pope Marcellinus begins his papacy.
events.html: • 296 – Pope Marcellinus begins his papacy.[1]

events.description: The Byzantine army of emperor Constantine V defeats the Bulgarian forces in the Battle of Anchialus.
events.html: • 763 – The Byzantine army of emperor Constantine V defeats the Bulgarian forces in the Battle of Anchialus.[2]

events.description: Battle of Arbedo between the duke of Milan and the Swiss cantons.
events.html: • 1422 – Battle of Arbedo between the duke of Milan and the Swiss cantons.[3]

events.description: Spanish forces defeat a combined French and Navarrese army at the Battle of Noáin during the Spanish conquest of Iberian Navarre.
events.html: • 1521 – Spanish forces defeat a combined French and Navarrese army at the Battle of Noáin during the Spanish conquest of Iberian Navarre.[4]

events.description: King Henry II of France is mortally wounded in a jousting match against Gabriel, comte de Montgomery.
events.html: • 1559 – King Henry II of France is mortally wounded in a jousting match against Gabriel, comte de Montgomery.[5]

events.description: The Spanish-held Castillo San Felipe del Morro in San Juan, Puerto Rico having been besieged for fifteen days, surrenders to an English force under Sir George Clifford, Earl of Cumberland.
events.html: • 1598 – The Spanish-held Castillo San Felipe del Morro in San Juan, Puerto Rico having been besieged for fifteen days, surrenders to an English force under Sir George Clifford, Earl of Cumberland.[6]

events.description: The University of Tartu is founded.
events.html: • 1632 – The University of Tartu is founded.[7]

events.description: The Deluge: Khmelnytsky Uprising: The Battle of Berestechko ends with a Polish victory.
events.html: • 1651 – The Deluge: Khmelnytsky Uprising: The Battle of Berestechko ends with a Polish victory.[8]

events.description: The Immortal Seven issue the Invitation to William, which would culminate in the Glorious Revolution.
events.html: • 1688 – The Immortal Seven issue the Invitation to William, which would culminate in the Glorious Revolution.[9]

events.description: The Battle of Ekeren between a Dutch force and a French force.
events.html: • 1703 – The Battle of Ekeren between a Dutch force and a French force.[10]

events.description: Seven Years' War: Habsburg Austrian forces destroy a Prussian reinforcement and supply convoy in the Battle of Domstadtl, helping to expel Prussian King Frederick the Great from Moravia.
events.html: • 1758 – Seven Years' War: Habsburg Austrian forces destroy a Prussian reinforcement and supply convoy in the Battle of Domstadtl, helping to expel Prussian King Frederick the Great from Moravia.[11]

events.description: Northwest Indian War: Native American forces under Blue Jacket attack Fort Recovery.
events.html: • 1794 – Northwest Indian War: Native American forces under Blue Jacket attack Fort Recovery.

events.description: Under An act to divide the Indiana Territory into two separate governments, adopted by the U.S. Congress on January 11, 1805, the Michigan Territory is organized.
events.html: • 1805 – Under An act to divide the Indiana Territory into two separate governments, adopted by the U.S. Congress on January 11, 1805, the Michigan Territory is organized.[12]

events.description: French acrobat Charles Blondin crosses Niagara Falls on a tightrope.
events.html: • 1859 – French acrobat Charles Blondin crosses Niagara Falls on a tightrope.

events.description: The 1860 Oxford evolution debate at the Oxford University Museum of Natural History takes place.
events.html: • 1860 – The 1860 Oxford evolution debate at the Oxford University Museum of Natural History takes place.

entities.name: Oxford University Museum of Natural History

events.description: U.S. President Abraham Lincoln grants Yosemite Valley to California for "public use, resort and recreation".
events.html: • 1864 – U.S. President Abraham Lincoln grants Yosemite Valley to California for "public use, resort and recreation".

events.description: Charles J. Guiteau is hanged in Washington, D.C. for the assassination of U.S. President James Garfield.
events.html: • 1882 – Charles J. Guiteau is hanged in Washington, D.C. for the assassination of U.S. President James Garfield.

events.description: The first transcontinental train trip across Canada departs from Montreal, Quebec. It arrives in Port Moody, British Columbia on July 4.
events.html: • 1886 – The first transcontinental train trip across Canada departs from Montreal, Quebec. It arrives in Port Moody, British Columbia on July 4.

events.description: The Homestead Strike begins near Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.
events.html: • 1892 – The Homestead Strike begins near Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.[13]

events.description: A savage fire wrecked three steamships docked at a pier in Hoboken, New Jersey. Over 200 crew members and passengers are killed, and hundreds injured.
events.html: • 1900 – A savage fire wrecked three steamships docked at a pier in Hoboken, New Jersey. Over 200 crew members and passengers are killed, and hundreds injured.[14]

events.description: Albert Einstein sends the article On the Electrodynamics of Moving Bodies, in which he introduces special relativity, for publication in Annalen der Physik.
events.html: • 1905 – Albert Einstein sends the article On the Electrodynamics of Moving Bodies, in which he introduces special relativity, for publication in Annalen der Physik.

entities.name: On the Electrodynamics of Moving Bodies

events.description: The United States Congress passes the Meat Inspection Act and Pure Food and Drug Act.
events.html: • 1906 – The United States Congress passes the Meat Inspection Act and Pure Food and Drug Act.

events.description: The Tunguska Event, the largest impact event on Earth in human recorded history, resulting in a massive explosion over Eastern Siberia.
events.html: • 1908 – The Tunguska Event, the largest impact event on Earth in human recorded history, resulting in a massive explosion over Eastern Siberia.

events.description: The Regina Cyclone, Canada's deadliest tornado event, kills 28 people in Regina, Saskatchewan.
events.html: • 1912 – The Regina Cyclone, Canada's deadliest tornado event, kills 28 people in Regina, Saskatchewan.

events.description: World War I: In "the day Sussex died", elements of the Royal Sussex Regiment take heavy casualties in the Battle of the Boar's Head at Richebourg-l'Avoué in France.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: In "the day Sussex died", elements of the Royal Sussex Regiment take heavy casualties in the Battle of the Boar's Head at Richebourg-l'Avoué in France.[15]

events.description: U.S. President Warren G. Harding appoints former President William Howard Taft as Chief Justice of the United States.
events.html: • 1921 – U.S. President Warren G. Harding appoints former President William Howard Taft as Chief Justice of the United States.

entities.name: Chief Justice of the United States

events.description: In Washington D.C., U.S. Secretary of State Charles Evans Hughes and Dominican Ambassador Francisco J. Peynado sign the Hughes–Peynado agreement, which ends the United States occupation of the Dominican Republic.
events.html: • 1922 – In Washington D.C., U.S. Secretary of State Charles Evans Hughes and Dominican Ambassador Francisco J. Peynado sign the Hughes–Peynado agreement, which ends the United States occupation of the Dominican Republic.

entities.name: United States occupation of the Dominican Republic (1916–24)

events.description: The Night of the Long Knives, Adolf Hitler's violent purge of his political rivals in Germany, takes place.
events.html: • 1934 – The Night of the Long Knives, Adolf Hitler's violent purge of his political rivals in Germany, takes place.

events.description: Emperor Haile Selassie of Abyssinia appeals for aid to the League of Nations against Italy's invasion of his country.
events.html: • 1936 – Emperor Haile Selassie of Abyssinia appeals for aid to the League of Nations against Italy's invasion of his country.

events.description: The world's first emergency telephone number, 999, is introduced in London.
events.html: • 1937 – The world's first emergency telephone number, 999, is introduced in London.

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Cherbourg ends with the fall of the strategically valuable port to American forces.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Battle of Cherbourg ends with the fall of the strategically valuable port to American forces.

events.description: The first Chevrolet Corvette rolls off the assembly line in Flint, Michigan.
events.html: • 1953 – The first Chevrolet Corvette rolls off the assembly line in Flint, Michigan.

events.description: A TWA Super Constellation and a United Airlines DC-7 collide above the Grand Canyon in Arizona and crash, killing all 128 on board both airliners.
events.html: • 1956 – A TWA Super Constellation and a United Airlines DC-7 collide above the Grand Canyon in Arizona and crash, killing all 128 on board both airliners.

events.description: A United States Air Force F-100 Super Sabre from Kadena Air Base, Okinawa, crashes into a nearby elementary school, killing 11 students plus six residents from the local neighborhood.
events.html: • 1959 – A United States Air Force F-100 Super Sabre from Kadena Air Base, Okinawa, crashes into a nearby elementary school, killing 11 students plus six residents from the local neighborhood.

events.description: Belgian Congo gains independence as Republic of the Congo (Léopoldville).
events.html: • 1960 – Belgian Congo gains independence as Republic of the Congo (Léopoldville).

events.description: Ciaculli bombing: a car bomb, intended for Mafia boss Salvatore Greco, kills seven police officers and military personnel near Palermo.
events.html: • 1963 – Ciaculli bombing: a car bomb, intended for Mafia boss Salvatore Greco, kills seven police officers and military personnel near Palermo.

events.description: The National Organization for Women, the United States' largest feminist organization, is founded.
events.html: • 1966 – The National Organization for Women, the United States' largest feminist organization, is founded.

events.description: Pope Paul VI issues the Credo of the People of God.
events.html: • 1968 – Pope Paul VI issues the Credo of the People of God.[16]

entities.name: Credo of the People of God

events.description: The crew of the Soviet Soyuz 11 spacecraft are killed when their air supply escapes through a faulty valve.
events.html: • 1971 – The crew of the Soviet Soyuz 11 spacecraft are killed when their air supply escapes through a faulty valve.[17]

events.description: The first leap second is added to the UTC time system.
events.html: • 1972 – The first leap second is added to the UTC time system.

events.description: Concorde 001 intercepts the path of a total solar eclipse and follows the moon's shadow, experiencing the longest total eclipse observation.
events.html: • 1973 – Concorde 001 intercepts the path of a total solar eclipse and follows the moon's shadow, experiencing the longest total eclipse observation.[18]

events.description: The Baltimore municipal strike of 1974 begins.
events.html: • 1974 – The Baltimore municipal strike of 1974 begins.[19]

events.description: The Southeast Asia Treaty Organization disbands.
events.html: • 1977 – The Southeast Asia Treaty Organization disbands.

events.description: Thirty-nine American hostages from the hijacked TWA Flight 847 are freed in Beirut after being held for 17 days.
events.html: • 1985 – Thirty-nine American hostages from the hijacked TWA Flight 847 are freed in Beirut after being held for 17 days.

events.description: The U.S. Supreme Court rules in Bowers v. Hardwick that states can outlaw homosexual acts between consenting adults.
events.html: • 1986 – The U.S. Supreme Court rules in Bowers v. Hardwick that states can outlaw homosexual acts between consenting adults.[20]

entities.name: Supreme Court of the United States

events.description: A coup d'état in Sudan deposes the democratically elected government of Prime Minister Sadiq al-Mahdi and President Ahmed al-Mirghani.
events.html: • 1989 – A coup d'état in Sudan deposes the democratically elected government of Prime Minister Sadiq al-Mahdi and President Ahmed al-Mirghani.[21]

events.description: East and West Germany merge their economies.
events.html: • 1990 – East and West Germany merge their economies.

events.description: Malta is officially subdivided into 68 local councils by the Local Councils Act.
events.html: • 1993 – Malta is officially subdivided into 68 local councils by the Local Councils Act.[22]

events.description: During a test flight of an Airbus A330-300 at Toulouse–Blagnac Airport, the aircraft crashes killing all seven people on board.
events.html: • 1994 – During a test flight of an Airbus A330-300 at Toulouse–Blagnac Airport, the aircraft crashes killing all seven people on board.[23]

events.description: A Jeep Cherokee filled with propane canisters drives into the entrance of Glasgow Airport, Scotland in a failed terrorist attack. This was linked to the 2007 London car bombs that had taken place the day before.
events.html: • 2007 – A Jeep Cherokee filled with propane canisters drives into the entrance of Glasgow Airport, Scotland in a failed terrorist attack. This was linked to the 2007 London car bombs that had taken place the day before.

events.description: Yemenia Flight 626, an Airbus A310-300, crashes into the Indian Ocean near Comoros, killing 152 of the 153 people on board. A 14-year-old girl named Bahia Bakari survives the crash.
events.html: • 2009 – Yemenia Flight 626, an Airbus A310-300, crashes into the Indian Ocean near Comoros, killing 152 of the 153 people on board. A 14-year-old girl named Bahia Bakari survives the crash.[24]

events.description: Nineteen firefighters die controlling a wildfire near Yarnell, Arizona.
events.html: • 2013 – Nineteen firefighters die controlling a wildfire near Yarnell, Arizona.

events.description: Protests begin around Egypt against President Mohamed Morsi and the ruling Freedom and Justice Party, leading to their overthrow during the 2013 Egyptian coup d'état.
events.html: • 2013 – Protests begin around Egypt against President Mohamed Morsi and the ruling Freedom and Justice Party, leading to their overthrow during the 2013 Egyptian coup d'état.

events.description: A Hercules C-130 military aircraft with 113 people on board crashes in a residential area in Medan, Indonesia, resulting in at least 116 deaths.

events.description: Donald Trump becomes the first sitting US President to visit the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (North Korea).
events.html: • 2019 – Donald Trump becomes the first sitting US President to visit the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (North Korea).[25]

events.description: The Tiger Fire ignites near Black Canyon City, Arizona, and goes on to burn 16,278 acres (6,587 ha) of land before being fully contained on July 30.
events.html: • 2021 – The Tiger Fire ignites near Black Canyon City, Arizona, and goes on to burn 16,278 acres (6,587 ha) of land before being fully contained on July 30.[26][27]
